Kali Linux is a Debian-derived Linux distribution designed for digital forensics and penetration testing.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
/bin:
    -is a standard subdirectory of the root directory in Unix-like operating systems that contains the executable(i.e., ready to run) programs that must be available in order to
     attain minimal functionality for the purposes of booting(i.e., starting) and repairing a system.
